      "question": "3. Why was this exact systemic dependency, resource limitation, or cryptographic incompatibility not mitigated before production exposure?",
      "answer": "The pre-production testing sandboxes utilized optimized local LAN connections with a uniform MTU size of 1,500 bytes and no security firewall block rules for fragmented packets. This testing environment failed to simulate tunnel overhead restrictions or account for the packet fragmentation mechanics encountered over WAN routing paths."
    },
    {
      "question": "4. Why did proactive automation validation, change window testing, or secondary workarounds fail to catch or stop this configuration drift?",
      "answer": "The automated group provisioning utilities evaluated success based entirely on database write confirmations within Active Directory. The post-change validation checklist did not include a network packet header analysis or cross-region tunnel test to evaluate the physical transport limits of expanded user tokens."
    },
