      "question": "5. Why was a permanent architectural upgrade, automated mapping, or infrastructure redundancy not successfully implemented beforehand?",
      "answer": "The network lifecycle framework lacked an integrated, automated process to dynamic-source client transport parameters based on active user token measurements. Protocol settings relied on old operating system defaults that assumed Kerberos transactions would fit cleanly within legacy UDP boundaries."
