  "corrective_preventive_actions": [
    {
      "action_type": "CA",
      "action_description": "The Active Directory Core Operations team executed immediate registry-level adjustments across all enterprise domain structures to eliminate the connection packet drops. Engineers configured a global group policy object override to adjust the 'MaxPacketSize' variable down to an absolute value of 1. This modification completely flushed the active fault state by forcing the localized client and server security providers to bypass UDP transport entirely for any Kerberos handshake. The change forced the immediate use of stream-oriented TCP port 88 for all Ticket Granting Service queries, effectively bypassing the firewall's UDP fragmentation filters. The updated policy was force-replicated across all global catalog nodes using system replication utilities. Remote client connections immediately stabilized, and subsequent packet analysis confirmed that connection timeouts dropped to zero.",
